.TH bashbi 7 2025-12-06
.SH NAME
.B bashbi
\- bash_builtin project coding guide
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This is an entry-point for Bash builtin man page references.
.PP
Since it is needed to develop Bash builtins, it is assumed
that the Bash builtins development package,
.B bash-builtins
is installed.  It is further assumed that the header files of
.B bash-builtins
are found in
.IR /usr/include/bash .
Adjust your search directory if your installation differs from
this assumption.
.PP
Topics will be covered in pages with
.B bashbi_
prefixes.
.SH TOPICS
.TP
.BR bashbi_vars (7)
Structure of
.B SHELL_VAR
from
.IR variables.h ,
along with a summary of important variable manipulation
functions.
.TP
.BR bashbi_internals (7)
A discussion of Bash resources that can be called from the
C code of a Bash builtin command.  This includes the steps
needed for calling a script function.
.TP
.BR bashbi_collections (7)
.IR "Comming Attraction" :
References to help construct various Bash collections, from script
declared
.BR ARRAY " and " HASH_TABLE
(associative arrays), to
.BR WORD_LIST ,
which is a linked-list of strings that is how Bash passes arguments
to compliant bash functions, including script functions and Bash
builtins.
